00:11:39,299 --> 00:11:40,600
there’s no discussion.

251
00:11:40,634 --> 00:11:43,070
- They’re killed on the spot.
- ( All gasp )

252
00:11:43,103 --> 00:11:45,906
Goreinu: They’ve also been
stealing all of their cards.

253
00:11:45,939 --> 00:11:47,174
Seems they’re totally focused

254
00:11:47,207 --> 00:11:49,076
on obtaining accompany
and magnetic force.

255
00:11:49,109 --> 00:11:50,410
And any players

256
00:11:50,444 --> 00:11:52,646
who are fully cleared
of suspicion and released

257
00:11:52,679 --> 00:11:55,081
are then forced
to collect cards for them.

258
00:11:55,115 --> 00:11:58,485
By eliminating suspects
and taking their cards,

259
00:11:58,519 --> 00:12:00,988
they’ve effectively
cut off our supply.

260
00:12:01,021 --> 00:12:03,290
They’re killing three birds
with one stone.

261
00:12:03,323 --> 00:12:05,025
Tsezguerra: Understood.

262
00:12:05,058 --> 00:12:07,494
We’ll try and keep track
of their movements from here.

263
00:12:07,528 --> 00:12:10,598
Get away from there now,
and wait for us to contact you.

264
00:12:11,632 --> 00:12:13,634
♪

265
00:12:19,239 --> 00:12:22,609
( Scanner beeping )

266
00:12:22,643 --> 00:12:25,646
Kess: They don’t appear
to be leaving masadora.

267
00:12:25,679 --> 00:12:28,415
Tsezguerra: Okay, so next
we’ll check on their cards.

268
00:12:30,050 --> 00:12:32,419
Rodriot: It looks like
the three of them

269
00:12:32,452 --> 00:12:35,355
have 16 accompanies
and two magnetic forces.

270
00:12:35,389 --> 00:12:37,091
Barry: They’ve gained a lot.

271
00:12:37,124 --> 00:12:38,626
Tsezguerra: At this rate,

272
00:12:38,659 --> 00:12:41,729
they’ll be caught up with us
in just four or five days,

273
00:12:41,762 --> 00:12:44,098
but that’s just about
what we expected.

274
00:12:44,131 --> 00:12:46,033
They don’t plan to move on

275
00:12:46,066 --> 00:12:47,501
until they’re
absolutely positive

276
00:12:47,534 --> 00:12:49,036
that they have enough cards.

277
00:12:49,069 --> 00:12:51,238
12 days left.

278
00:12:51,271 --> 00:12:53,440
We’re right on schedule.

279
00:12:53,473 --> 00:12:55,442
( Gon grunting )

280
00:12:55,475 --> 00:12:57,978
♪

281
00:12:58,011 --> 00:12:59,546
Hah!

282
00:13:01,682 --> 00:13:03,284
( Groans )

283
00:13:03,317 --> 00:13:05,152
I just can’t do it.

284
00:13:08,088 --> 00:13:12,159
Bisky: When training, visualize
yourself firing a water pistol.

285
00:13:12,192 --> 00:13:16,029
Gather your aura. Then shoot it
all out of your palm at once.

286
00:13:16,063 --> 00:13:18,365
The greater the force
you’re able to summon,

287
00:13:18,398 --> 00:13:21,468
the more striking power
the emitted aura will have.

288
00:13:21,502 --> 00:13:25,139
Open up the nodes in your hand,
and emit the aura.

289
00:13:25,172 --> 00:13:27,641
The amount of refined aura
that you apply,

290
00:13:27,674 --> 00:13:29,476
the speed and the power--

291
00:13:29,510 --> 00:13:31,412
oh, yes, and timing--

292
00:13:31,445 --> 00:13:33,647
all of these elements
must be present,

293
00:13:33,680 --> 00:13:36,283
or else you won’t get the effect
you’re looking for.

294
00:13:37,317 --> 00:13:39,219
Gon: It’s too hard!

295
00:13:39,253 --> 00:13:41,422
I get all
the other stuff from before,

296
00:13:41,455 --> 00:13:44,291
but not how you push it
out of your hand.

297
00:13:44,324 --> 00:13:47,494
Killua: He hasn’t
made any progress for ten days.

298
00:13:47,528 --> 00:13:49,430
Maybe you should
have allowed him

299
00:13:49,463 --> 00:13:51,665
to pick it up
from level two after all.

300
00:13:51,698 --> 00:13:53,633
Bisky: We still have
ten more days.

301
00:13:53,667 --> 00:13:56,503
Killua: Yeah, only if
team tsezguerra can deliver.

302
00:13:56,537 --> 00:14:00,374
Looking back on it now, it
wasn’t a very good deal for us.

303
00:14:00,407 --> 00:14:02,643
If we hand over
wild luck alexandrite,

304
00:14:02,676 --> 00:14:04,745
they’re only gonna
be missing two cards.

305
00:14:04,778 --> 00:14:08,315
We still need over 30, and
that’s gonna take us a while.

306
00:14:08,348 --> 00:14:10,784
Bisky: We can just take them
from genthru by force.

307
00:14:10,817 --> 00:14:12,118
It’s not a problem.

308
00:14:12,152 --> 00:14:14,121
Killua: Gon would
never accept that.

309
00:14:14,154 --> 00:14:18,125
Besides, we still have to figure
out how to beat genthru first.

310
00:14:18,158 --> 00:14:20,527
- Bisky: Yes, that’s true.
- ( Gon grunting )

311
00:14:20,561 --> 00:14:23,731
Bisky: So do you think
this is big enough?

312
00:14:24,765 --> 00:14:25,766
Killua: Yeah.

313
00:14:26,767 --> 00:14:29,336
( Birds squawk )

314
00:14:29,369 --> 00:14:33,340
Genthru: We now have
48 copies of accompany.

315
00:14:33,373 --> 00:14:36,243
If you add up
all their accompany, return,

316
00:14:36,276 --> 00:14:39,546
and magnetic force cards,
they only have 45.

317
00:14:39,580 --> 00:14:42,550
- They can’t shake us now.
- ( Both chuckle )

318
00:14:42,583 --> 00:14:47,755
Genthru: So I suggest we start
a game of tag we can’t lose.

319
00:14:47,788 --> 00:14:50,291
Accompany on! Tsezguerra!

320
00:14:50,324 --> 00:14:52,159
♪

321
00:14:52,192 --> 00:14:53,660
Kess: They’re on the way,

322
00:14:53,694 --> 00:14:55,362
and their speed is unbelievable!

323
00:14:56,830 --> 00:14:58,565
Tsezguerra: Stick to the plan!

324
00:15:06,807 --> 00:15:09,476
Tsezguerra:
Accompany on! To masadora!

325
00:15:11,512 --> 00:15:13,681
Genthru:
Accompany on! Tsezguerra!

326
00:15:20,521 --> 00:15:23,691
Tsezguerra: Accompany on!
To soufrabi!

327
00:15:23,724 --> 00:15:26,193
Genthru: Accompany on!
Tsezguerra!

328
00:15:29,830 --> 00:15:32,232
Tsezguerra: Accompany on!
To masadora!

329
00:15:32,266 --> 00:15:34,802
Genthru:
Accompany on! Tsezguerra!

330
00:15:34,835 --> 00:15:36,737
♪

331
00:15:44,645 --> 00:15:46,747
Tsezguerra: I’m all out. Barry!

332
00:15:46,780 --> 00:15:47,748
Barry: Roger.

333
00:15:47,781 --> 00:15:51,151
Accompany on! To soufrabi!

334
00:15:51,185 --> 00:15:53,754
( Gon grunting )

335
00:15:53,787 --> 00:15:57,624
Damn! We’ve only
got five days left!

336
00:15:57,658 --> 00:15:59,693
Killua: Don’t you have
a little bit of advice

337
00:15:59,726 --> 00:16:01,361
that might help him
to break through?

338
00:16:01,395 --> 00:16:04,498
Bisky: The sensation of aura
flowing through the body

339
00:16:04,531 --> 00:16:06,767
is similar,
but different for everyone.

340
00:16:06,800 --> 00:16:11,171
All I can do is try to give him
advice from my own perspective,

341
00:16:11,205 --> 00:16:13,774
but he might make
the wrong assumptions. You know.

342
00:16:13,807 --> 00:16:14,775
( Killua sighs )

343
00:16:14,808 --> 00:16:16,810
Gon: Hah!

344
00:16:16,844 --> 00:16:18,546
Damn it.

345
00:16:18,579 --> 00:16:19,580
Hah!

346
00:16:20,814 --> 00:16:22,282
Tsezguerra: How many left?

347
00:16:22,316 --> 00:16:24,185
Barry: Seven copies
of accompany.

348
00:16:24,218 --> 00:16:26,787
Rodriot: They’re not coming.
You think they gave up?

349
00:16:26,820 --> 00:16:28,388
Tsezguerra: No way.

350
00:16:28,422 --> 00:16:30,858
They’re just taking their time
to throw us off.

351
00:16:30,891 --> 00:16:33,694
Kess: If we run out
of accompany, we have return.

352
00:16:33,727 --> 00:16:35,963
Rodriot: Then we’ll alternate
between aiai and soufrabi.

353
00:16:35,996 --> 00:16:37,798
Barry: How is it over there?

354
00:16:37,831 --> 00:16:40,334
Tsezguerra: Let’s find out.

355
00:16:40,367 --> 00:16:43,203
And contact on. Goreinu.

356
00:16:43,237 --> 00:16:46,207
It’s tsezguerra. How’s it going?

357
00:16:46,240 --> 00:16:48,209
Goreinu: Looks like
you were right.

358
00:16:48,242 --> 00:16:50,678
Sub and bara showed up,

359
00:16:50,711 --> 00:16:53,214
most likely the real ones.

360
00:16:53,247 --> 00:16:54,882
They might be speculating

361
00:16:54,915 --> 00:16:57,418
that i’ll try to buy cards
while they’re off playing tag.

362
00:16:57,451 --> 00:16:59,787
That means that the ones
who are chasing you

363
00:16:59,820 --> 00:17:01,722
are genthru
and a couple of fakes.

364
00:17:01,755 --> 00:17:03,590
Rodriot: It sounds like
your predictions

365
00:17:03,624 --> 00:17:04,959
were pretty accurate.

366
00:17:04,992 --> 00:17:06,727
Tsezguerra: That same trick
won’t work again.

367
00:17:06,760 --> 00:17:10,264
Kess: There are four of us,
and genthru’s all by himself.

368
00:17:10,297 --> 00:17:12,432
If you ask me, now’s our chance.

369
00:17:12,466 --> 00:17:13,867
Tsezguerra: Not yet.

370
00:17:13,901 --> 00:17:16,637
I’d prefer much better odds
before we fight them.

371
00:17:16,670 --> 00:17:18,872
We’ll stick to the plan.

372
00:17:18,906 --> 00:17:22,243
( Spell whooshing )

373
00:17:22,276 --> 00:17:24,278
Here they come. We’re back on!

374
00:17:25,679 --> 00:17:27,648
- Gon: Hah!
- ( Aura whooshes )

375
00:17:27,681 --> 00:17:28,815
( Gasping )

376
00:17:28,849 --> 00:17:30,250
Killua: Gon.

377
00:17:30,284 --> 00:17:33,454
Your time’s up.
Training’s over.

378
00:17:33,487 --> 00:17:35,522
Gon: But we still
have five days!

379
00:17:35,556 --> 00:17:37,324
Killua: Had a change in plans.

380
00:17:37,357 --> 00:17:39,526
We’ve formed a new strategy
to defeat them.

381
00:17:39,560 --> 00:17:40,961
Gon: Yeah, but hold on.

382
00:17:40,994 --> 00:17:42,963
See, the thing is

383
00:17:42,996 --> 00:17:46,032
I think i’m getting
really close, maybe.

384
00:17:46,066 --> 00:17:48,835
Killua: Not happening.
I can’t base our whole strategy

385
00:17:48,869 --> 00:17:51,472
on a new technique
that isn’t reliable yet.

386
00:17:51,505 --> 00:17:52,973
- Just give up.
- ( Gon groans )

387
00:17:53,006 --> 00:17:55,275
Killua: Okay. So the plan is--

388
00:17:55,309 --> 00:17:56,777
bisky: To use this card.

389
00:17:56,810 --> 00:17:58,512
Gon: Eh?

390
00:17:58,545 --> 00:18:00,714
Killua: You’ll have to learn it
the hard way.

391
00:18:00,747 --> 00:18:02,716
Practice ’til you’ve
got it perfect.

392
00:18:02,749 --> 00:18:03,717
Gon: Uh...

393
00:18:03,750 --> 00:18:06,419
( Spell whooshing )

394
00:18:06,453 --> 00:18:08,555
Barry: We’re out of accompanies.

395
00:18:08,589 --> 00:18:09,824
Tsezguerra: Use return.

396
00:18:12,659 --> 00:18:15,862
All: Return on! To aiai!

397
00:18:17,831 --> 00:18:20,500
Genthru: They’re out
of accompanies, are they?

398
00:18:20,534 --> 00:18:22,569
Endgame’s almost upon us.

399
00:18:23,604 --> 00:18:24,605
Sub, bara,

400
00:18:24,638 --> 00:18:25,806
have you caught anyone?

401
00:18:25,839 --> 00:18:27,407
Sub: Yeah, but just one.

402
00:18:27,441 --> 00:18:30,577
And it was a newbie,
so he was pretty inexperienced.

403
00:18:30,611 --> 00:18:34,482
Word got out that the bombers
are hunting players,

404
00:18:34,515 --> 00:18:35,983
so everyone’s staying clear.

405
00:18:37,117 --> 00:18:39,086
Well, what do you think?

406
00:18:39,119 --> 00:18:40,988
Could he have been
someone we’ve already killed?

407
00:18:41,021 --> 00:18:43,390
Genthru: Perhaps.

408
00:18:43,423 --> 00:18:45,325
All right, just come back
when you’re ready.

409
00:18:45,359 --> 00:18:47,361
I’m in soufrabi right now.

410
00:18:47,394 --> 00:18:48,896
( Fakes whimper )

411
00:18:48,929 --> 00:18:51,899
Genthru: It seems they’ve
run out of ammunition.

412
00:18:52,933 --> 00:18:55,903
♪

413
00:18:55,936 --> 00:18:58,705
Tsezguerra:
We’re on our last card.

414
00:18:58,739 --> 00:19:01,008
If they try to follow us
outside the game,

415
00:19:01,041 --> 00:19:02,976
we can just hole up
at the mansion.

416
00:19:03,010 --> 00:19:04,678
Rodriot: And if
they don’t follow us,

417
00:19:04,711 --> 00:19:06,513
we just have
to run out the clock.

418
00:19:06,547 --> 00:19:07,915
Kess: This is perfect.

419
00:19:07,948 --> 00:19:10,584
Let’s pick the cards
we’ll keep once we win.

420
00:19:10,617 --> 00:19:11,918
Barry: Before we do,

421
00:19:11,952 --> 00:19:14,521
we should ask Mr. Battera
which ones he wants.

422
00:19:14,555 --> 00:19:16,757
( Spell whooshing )

423
00:19:16,790 --> 00:19:18,525
Tsezguerra: All right! Let’s go!

424
00:19:18,559 --> 00:19:20,461
Leave on!

425
00:19:36,076 --> 00:19:37,544
Rodriot: Nobody’s in here.

426
00:19:37,578 --> 00:19:39,046
Kess: Wait. What’s going on?

427
00:19:39,079 --> 00:19:41,848
There were supposed
to be armed guards.

428
00:19:41,882 --> 00:19:43,117
Tsezguerra: Where are you?

429
00:19:43,150 --> 00:19:45,452
Speak up! Hey, sabazushi!

430
00:19:45,485 --> 00:19:47,387
Answer me!

431
00:19:47,421 --> 00:19:49,456
Sabazushi: Keep it down.

432
00:19:49,489 --> 00:19:52,459
Some of us were trying
to catch a nap here.

433
00:19:52,492 --> 00:19:53,660
Tsezguerra: You were sleeping?

434
00:19:53,694 --> 00:19:55,729
What the hell
happened to everyone else?

435
00:19:55,762 --> 00:19:57,664
- Sabazushi: Oh, they all left.
- Tsezguerra: Huh?

436
00:19:57,698 --> 00:20:00,434
Sabazushi: Mr. Battera
scrapped the whole thing.

437
00:20:00,467 --> 00:20:03,670
We received a cancellation fee
and an intermediary fee,

438
00:20:03,704 --> 00:20:06,440
but I stuck around
to let you know.

439
00:20:07,674 --> 00:20:09,576
Tsezguerra: It was canceled?

440
00:20:10,811 --> 00:20:13,747
Mr. Battera,
what is the meaning of this?!

441
00:20:13,780 --> 00:20:17,917
We’ve come so far.
We’ve almost beaten the game!

442
00:20:17,951 --> 00:20:21,621
Battera: It doesn’t matter,
not anymore.

443
00:20:21,655 --> 00:20:22,789
( Tsezguerra groans )

444
00:20:22,823 --> 00:20:24,925
"Doesn’t matter"? What is that?!

445
00:20:24,958 --> 00:20:27,928
What about all the time
and effort we spent?!

446
00:20:27,961 --> 00:20:31,932
Battera: My lawyers have been
instructed to pay you.

447
00:20:31,965 --> 00:20:36,937
As for the cards,
do with them as you wish.

448
00:20:36,970 --> 00:20:39,105
So now, please,

449
00:20:39,139 --> 00:20:42,943
I just want to be left alone,
I beg you.

450
00:20:42,976 --> 00:20:44,945
( Tsezguerra groans )

451
00:20:44,978 --> 00:20:46,546
Damn it!

452
00:20:46,580 --> 00:20:48,549
Kess: You find out
what’s happening?

453
00:20:48,582 --> 00:20:49,950
Tsezguerra: No idea,

454
00:20:49,983 --> 00:20:52,586
but i’m determined to find out.

455
00:20:52,619 --> 00:20:53,854
- ( Explosion )
- ( Sabazushi screams )

456
00:20:53,887 --> 00:20:55,255
( Gurgles )

457
00:20:56,790 --> 00:20:59,760
Genthru: We can kill
all we want out here,

458
00:20:59,793 --> 00:21:02,763
since we won’t lose
any ring data.

459
00:21:02,796 --> 00:21:04,865
( Chuckles )

460
00:21:07,067 --> 00:21:10,037
Narrator: Team tsezguerra
his given gon and his friends

461
00:21:10,070 --> 00:21:11,872
the time they’d promised,

462
00:21:11,905 --> 00:21:13,507
but waiting for them

463
00:21:13,540 --> 00:21:16,043
was a situation
they did not expect.

464
00:21:16,076 --> 00:21:17,044
♪

465
00:21:17,077 --> 00:21:19,079
( Singing in Japanese )

